1
00:00:03,754 --> 00:00:07,216
It is time for war.

2
00:00:07,299 --> 00:00:09,552
- Help.
-  Better to stay hidden

3
00:00:09,635 --> 00:00:11,303
and wait for him to recover.

4
00:00:11,387 --> 00:00:13,305
You said
you didn't love my other mom.

5
00:00:13,389 --> 00:00:14,974
My real mom.

6
00:00:15,057 --> 00:00:16,767
That she was a mistake.

7
00:00:16,851 --> 00:00:18,728
Am I a mistake, too?

8
00:00:18,811 --> 00:00:20,438
I'll always find my way back to you.

9
00:00:20,521 --> 00:00:22,773
I'm gonna miss it here.

10
00:00:22,857 --> 00:00:25,109
You were out almost two months.

11
00:00:25,192 --> 00:00:27,737
Thaedus believes
he has won this war.

12
00:00:27,820 --> 00:00:31,115
That he and his allies are safe
on his adopted planet.

13
00:00:35,286 --> 00:00:36,746
Thragg's returning to Viltrum.

14
00:00:36,829 --> 00:00:38,414
He's gonna regroup there.

15
00:00:38,497 --> 00:00:41,584
If we strike Thragg now,
before he's joined

16
00:00:41,667 --> 00:00:43,377
by his remaining forces,

17
00:00:43,461 --> 00:00:47,173
we may have a chance
to end this war forever.

18
00:01:44,522 --> 00:01:47,066
This is the third act of sabotage

19
00:01:47,149 --> 00:01:49,985
by the Relonian natives this week.

20
00:01:50,069 --> 00:01:52,696
The species remains unusually defiant,

21
00:01:52,780 --> 00:01:56,951
despite our clear demonstrations
of Viltrumite superiority.

22
00:01:57,034 --> 00:02:00,412
I recommend
a planet-wide cull of the population

23
00:02:00,496 --> 00:02:03,999
before they disrupt
our mining operations any further.

24
00:02:04,083 --> 00:02:06,919
They resist us because we are occupiers

25
00:02:07,002 --> 00:02:09,630
and we are cruel.

26
00:02:09,713 --> 00:02:11,966
If we restrain ourselves,

27
00:02:12,049 --> 00:02:16,011
their labor will only aid in our goals.

28
00:02:16,095 --> 00:02:19,765
Their labor is nothing
without their fear and respect.

29
00:02:19,849 --> 00:02:21,725
Decimation sets an example,

30
00:02:21,809 --> 00:02:26,063
not only for them,
but for the next misguided species.

31
00:02:26,146 --> 00:02:27,731
Misguided?

32
00:02:27,815 --> 00:02:31,026
Do Viltrumites not respect strength?

33
00:02:31,110 --> 00:02:34,154
The courage
to challenge one's oppressors?

34
00:02:34,238 --> 00:02:37,408
They are nothing to us.

35
00:02:37,491 --> 00:02:39,702
The fact
that you believe otherwise makes me--

36
00:02:43,289 --> 00:02:45,040
Regent Thragg.

37
00:02:46,041 --> 00:02:48,043
Emperor Argall.

38
00:02:48,127 --> 00:02:49,712
What is your counsel?

39
00:02:51,213 --> 00:02:55,134
Thaedus, you say
Viltrumites respect strength.

40
00:02:55,217 --> 00:02:57,219
That is correct. We do.

41
00:02:57,303 --> 00:02:59,722
But these creatures,

42
00:02:59,805 --> 00:03:03,017
their strength is not true strength.

43
00:03:03,100 --> 00:03:07,187
We must educate them
not because of their defiance,

44
00:03:07,271 --> 00:03:11,108
but because their weakness is an offense
to the natural order of the universe.

45
00:03:11,191 --> 00:03:12,943
You are young, Regent.

46
00:03:13,027 --> 00:03:15,696
Perhaps you do not yet
see the longer game--

47
00:03:15,779 --> 00:03:17,615
Regent Thragg is correct.

48
00:03:18,908 --> 00:03:22,286
Reduce the planet's population by 25%.

49
00:03:23,412 --> 00:03:25,372
If they continue to resist,

50
00:03:25,456 --> 00:03:27,082
eradicate them.

51
00:03:28,167 --> 00:03:31,795
Emperor, I urge you to reconsider.

52
00:03:33,964 --> 00:03:35,049
Do you?

53
00:03:43,182 --> 00:03:46,477
Thaedus and I fought
side by side at Capida Minor.

54
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:49,563
He was the strongest among our company,

55
00:03:49,647 --> 00:03:51,190
the most ruthless.

56
00:03:51,273 --> 00:03:55,945
Yet ever since he returned
from his years in the Lay quadrant,

57
00:03:56,028 --> 00:03:58,197
he speaks of mercy

58
00:03:58,280 --> 00:04:00,824
and questions our ways.

59
00:04:00,908 --> 00:04:02,284
It is troubling.

60
00:04:15,673 --> 00:04:19,843
If you feel his weakness harms the empire,

61
00:04:19,927 --> 00:04:21,929
take action.

62
00:04:24,598 --> 00:04:27,726
Perhaps I am... mistaken.

63
00:05:29,038 --> 00:05:32,374
Emperor Argall showed us our strength,

64
00:05:32,458 --> 00:05:35,335
taught us our greatness,

65
00:05:35,419 --> 00:05:38,422
gave us our destiny.

66
00:05:38,505 --> 00:05:42,885
Because of him, all is ours.

67
00:05:43,677 --> 00:05:46,138
All is ours.

68
00:05:46,221 --> 00:05:49,099
The traitor has fled, but he will be found

69
00:05:49,183 --> 00:05:51,685
and pay the price for his treason.

70
00:05:51,769 --> 00:05:53,437
Be sure of that.

71
00:05:54,772 --> 00:05:58,776
Even in death, Emperor Argall shows us

72
00:05:58,859 --> 00:06:02,905
there is a sickness in our society,

73
00:06:02,988 --> 00:06:05,908
poisoning us from within.

74
00:06:05,991 --> 00:06:10,370
We will cut this cancer out.

75
00:06:11,455 --> 00:06:15,209
You. Might you also betray us someday?

76
00:06:16,043 --> 00:06:18,337
I will not, Grand Regent.

77
00:06:20,339 --> 00:06:22,591
I do not believe you.

78
00:06:38,190 --> 00:06:40,609
As our customs dictate,

79
00:06:40,692 --> 00:06:42,361
I now assume the throne

80
00:06:42,444 --> 00:06:44,988
as Grand Regent of Viltrum
until one of Argall's

81
00:06:45,072 --> 00:06:47,449
heirs can be found.

82
00:06:48,659 --> 00:06:50,953
This is my first command.

83
00:06:52,329 --> 00:06:55,791
Seek out the weakness
that allowed this betrayal...

84
00:06:58,252 --> 00:07:02,464
...and purge it from our midst.

85
00:09:45,210 --> 00:09:47,713
Yes.

86
00:09:47,796 --> 00:09:48,880
No.

87
00:09:53,260 --> 00:09:55,012
It is done.

88
00:10:01,810 --> 00:10:03,770
I will not repeat myself.

89
00:10:09,151 --> 00:10:11,778
Yes, Grand Regent.

90
00:10:15,991 --> 00:10:20,704
The blood
that ran through our streets

91
00:10:20,787 --> 00:10:22,873
has cleansed us.

92
00:10:23,874 --> 00:10:27,669
For you, the strong,

93
00:10:27,753 --> 00:10:30,422
your life is its own reward.

94
00:10:30,505 --> 00:10:33,675
But our work is not yet done.

95
00:10:33,759 --> 00:10:36,303
For even in death,

96
00:10:36,386 --> 00:10:39,264
Argall still guides us.

97
00:10:40,766 --> 00:10:42,100
We will follow his path

98
00:10:42,184 --> 00:10:46,271
and take our place
as the rightful rulers of the galaxy.

99
00:10:46,355 --> 00:10:49,316
The universe itself will kneel.

100
00:10:50,567 --> 00:10:53,070
As it was meant to be.

101
00:10:53,153 --> 00:10:56,323
All is ours.

102
00:10:57,741 --> 00:11:00,535
All is ours!

103
00:11:00,619 --> 00:11:03,538
All is ours!

104
00:11:03,622 --> 00:11:06,541
All is ours! All...

105
00:11:06,625 --> 00:11:08,502
is ours!

106
00:11:21,598 --> 00:11:23,558
I failed you, my emperor.

107
00:11:26,186 --> 00:11:28,146
But I will not fail our people.

108
00:11:29,523 --> 00:11:31,024
Not again.

109
00:11:35,487 --> 00:11:37,864
All our intelligence agrees.

110
00:11:37,948 --> 00:11:42,077
Thragg has retreated to Viltrum
with no more than a few of his people.

111
00:11:42,160 --> 00:11:44,246
The rest are on their way there,

112
00:11:44,329 --> 00:11:46,623
but will not arrive for several days.

113
00:11:46,706 --> 00:11:49,709
This is our chance,

114
00:11:49,793 --> 00:11:53,588
a brief moment
when the regent is vulnerable.

115
00:11:53,672 --> 00:11:56,425
Um, Great Thaedus?

116
00:11:56,508 --> 00:11:59,136
Don't get me wrong,
I would love to kill Thragg

117
00:11:59,219 --> 00:12:01,596
for, like, a million reasons.
But won't that still leave us

118
00:12:01,680 --> 00:12:05,183
with 40-something extra pissed-off
Viltrumites out for revenge?

119
00:12:05,267 --> 00:12:08,520
Since the assassination of Emperor Argall,

120
00:12:08,603 --> 00:12:10,772
they have known no leader but Thragg.

121
00:12:11,815 --> 00:12:15,777
His loss will leave them
weak and directionless,

122
00:12:15,861 --> 00:12:19,489
fighting amongst themselves
as they did before.

123
00:12:20,532 --> 00:12:22,617
It will not be easy,

124
00:12:22,701 --> 00:12:27,372
but once Thragg is gone,
the others will fall one by one.

125
00:12:28,915 --> 00:12:32,377
Alone, Thragg could defeat any one of us.

126
00:12:32,461 --> 00:12:37,591
But together,
we have a chance to end this war forever.

127
00:12:37,674 --> 00:12:39,885
The future of the galaxy

128
00:12:39,968 --> 00:12:42,220
depends on us,

129
00:12:42,304 --> 00:12:45,098
and we may not all return.

130
00:12:46,099 --> 00:12:48,852
But it is worth any price

131
00:12:48,935 --> 00:12:53,982
to show the Viltrum Empire,
once and for all,

132
00:12:54,065 --> 00:12:58,278
that even their strength
does not make them...

133
00:13:05,368 --> 00:13:07,412
We're on our way
to fight this Thragg guy.

134
00:13:08,288 --> 00:13:10,415
Um, it's just him,

135
00:13:10,499 --> 00:13:12,959
plus two or three others,

136
00:13:13,043 --> 00:13:16,588
versus eight of us, so... easy, right?

137
00:13:16,671 --> 00:13:19,716
But apparently,
he was specially trained from birth

138
00:13:19,799 --> 00:13:21,843
to be the strongest Viltrumite ever.

139
00:13:22,969 --> 00:13:25,305
Even my dad's freaking out
about facing him.

140
00:13:26,765 --> 00:13:28,266
Eve, I don't know.

141
00:13:29,392 --> 00:13:31,853
This feels, uh...

142
00:13:31,937 --> 00:13:34,105
this feels different.

143
00:13:34,189 --> 00:13:36,274
And it's my last chance
to record a message for you

144
00:13:36,358 --> 00:13:38,235
just in case something happens,

145
00:13:38,318 --> 00:13:39,778
and, um...

146
00:13:41,780 --> 00:13:43,490
You know what?

147
00:13:43,573 --> 00:13:45,450
You're never even gonna see this because

148
00:13:45,534 --> 00:13:48,036
I love you and I'm coming back.

149
00:13:51,081 --> 00:13:53,083
I cannot believe it. You, too?

150
00:13:53,166 --> 00:13:56,545
I didn't say they were gross.
I said I didn't want one.

151
00:13:56,628 --> 00:13:58,713
Yeah, I know. No one does.

152
00:13:58,797 --> 00:14:00,590
Hey, I'll eat anything.

153
00:14:00,674 --> 00:14:03,552
My dad calls me
the human garbage disposal.

154
00:14:03,635 --> 00:14:07,138
I just never have
much of an appetite when I'm nervous.

155
00:14:07,222 --> 00:14:09,683
Also, those things have faces.

156
00:14:10,684 --> 00:14:12,394
Your moo-cows have faces.

157
00:14:12,477 --> 00:14:16,523
Okay, first, no one older than three
calls them "moo-cows."

158
00:14:16,606 --> 00:14:20,485
And second, they don't have faces
when I eat them.

159
00:14:24,614 --> 00:14:27,701
Why is everyone so nervous
about fighting this Thragg guy?

160
00:14:27,784 --> 00:14:29,578
No way he lives up to the hype.

161
00:14:29,661 --> 00:14:31,621
You haven't seen the reports.

162
00:14:31,705 --> 00:14:33,081
What do they say?

163
00:14:33,164 --> 00:14:34,791
That he lives up to the hype.

164
00:14:34,874 --> 00:14:36,835
We'll see.

165
00:14:39,254 --> 00:14:40,547
You guys are all crazy.

166
00:14:40,630 --> 00:14:41,840
You gotta eat something.

167
00:14:41,923 --> 00:14:44,593
The Unopan is correct.

168
00:14:44,676 --> 00:14:48,179
We must nourish ourselves before battle.

169
00:14:48,263 --> 00:14:52,767
Later, we will feast
on our enemies' entrails.

170
00:14:52,851 --> 00:14:55,312
Or they on ours.

171
00:14:57,022 --> 00:14:59,566
So this might be our last meal, huh?

172
00:15:01,776 --> 00:15:04,237
Fantastic.

173
00:15:04,321 --> 00:15:07,699
If you could eat anything
right now, what would it be?

174
00:15:07,782 --> 00:15:09,618
Burger Mart drive-thru.

175
00:15:09,701 --> 00:15:12,954
Boom. Triple triple. Yes.

176
00:15:13,038 --> 00:15:15,790
Ooh, with loaded fries
from the secret menu.

177
00:15:15,874 --> 00:15:17,876
It's my thing with my dad.

178
00:15:17,959 --> 00:15:21,046
Actually, if I really had to pick,

179
00:15:21,129 --> 00:15:23,965
Paul's spaghetti.
He's my mom's boyfriend.

180
00:15:24,049 --> 00:15:26,134
He makes his own meatballs
and everything.

181
00:15:27,052 --> 00:15:30,055
Mm. The Brain Bowl at the Galactic Grill.

182
00:15:31,931 --> 00:15:34,184
I am already eating it.

183
00:15:34,267 --> 00:15:37,437
My final meal will be my own blood,

184
00:15:37,520 --> 00:15:41,232
as I choke on it, breathing my last breath

185
00:15:41,316 --> 00:15:44,986
after a legendary battle
with a superior opponent.

186
00:15:46,404 --> 00:15:49,658
That will be a satisfying meal indeed.

187
00:15:56,831 --> 00:15:58,166
Mmm!

188
00:15:58,249 --> 00:15:59,751
Right?

189
00:16:01,753 --> 00:16:03,713
You seem worried, Nolan.

190
00:16:03,797 --> 00:16:05,507
I am.

191
00:16:06,841 --> 00:16:08,968
You should be, too.

192
00:16:09,052 --> 00:16:12,013
This is the best chance
we've had in centuries

193
00:16:12,097 --> 00:16:13,723
to end this conflict.

194
00:16:13,807 --> 00:16:16,434
But that is not what troubles you.

195
00:16:17,769 --> 00:16:19,145
No.

196
00:16:19,229 --> 00:16:21,314
Thragg must die.

197
00:16:21,398 --> 00:16:23,441
But the other Viltrumites...

198
00:16:23,525 --> 00:16:24,943
You said it yourself,

199
00:16:25,026 --> 00:16:27,779
they'll be weak and scattered
without him.

200
00:16:27,862 --> 00:16:31,700
And yet, still capable
of untold death and destruction.

201
00:16:32,909 --> 00:16:35,787
I will not risk even the smallest chance

202
00:16:35,870 --> 00:16:38,206
their empire could rise again.

203
00:16:40,709 --> 00:16:44,713
Mark and Oliver are part Viltrumite, too.

204
00:16:45,964 --> 00:16:49,050
Everyone, we've reached
Viltrum's sensor range.

205
00:16:49,134 --> 00:16:50,927
Time to get ready.

206
00:16:56,683 --> 00:16:58,393
We've only got ten of these?

207
00:16:58,476 --> 00:17:00,687
You have no idea
how difficult that sinlak poison

208
00:17:00,770 --> 00:17:03,189
was to extract and refine.

209
00:17:03,273 --> 00:17:05,817
Ah. Soon.

210
00:17:13,616 --> 00:17:15,243
Thaedus is coming too?

211
00:17:16,453 --> 00:17:17,746
He's, like, a million years...

212
00:17:18,913 --> 00:17:20,165
...old.

213
00:17:20,248 --> 00:17:21,708
Never mind.

214
00:17:21,791 --> 00:17:23,126
Listen to me.

215
00:17:23,209 --> 00:17:25,128
However strong you think you are,

216
00:17:25,211 --> 00:17:27,839
Thragg is stronger.

217
00:17:27,922 --> 00:17:30,091
Don't let him draw you
away from the group.

218
00:17:30,175 --> 00:17:33,553
That also means you don't
try to take him on alone, Oliver.

219
00:17:33,636 --> 00:17:34,804
I won't.

220
00:17:34,888 --> 00:17:36,639
We stick together.

221
00:17:36,723 --> 00:17:38,349
That's how we win this.

222
00:17:39,476 --> 00:17:41,895
If anything happens,

223
00:17:41,978 --> 00:17:43,605
just remember I...

224
00:17:45,273 --> 00:17:46,983
Ah...

225
00:17:48,485 --> 00:17:49,903
We know.

226
00:17:58,995 --> 00:18:01,498
I am gonna be so bummed
if I don't survive this.

227
00:18:04,167 --> 00:18:06,044
Is everyone ready?

228
00:18:06,127 --> 00:18:08,546
Stick to the plan.

229
00:18:08,630 --> 00:18:10,715
Sneak in past their sensors,

230
00:18:10,799 --> 00:18:13,593
then scour the planet
as quickly as possible.

231
00:18:14,594 --> 00:18:17,972
You all have coordinates
for the regent's most likely locations.

232
00:18:18,056 --> 00:18:19,974
When you find him,

233
00:18:20,058 --> 00:18:22,227
call in everyone else.

234
00:18:22,310 --> 00:18:25,563
Remember, Thragg's death

235
00:18:25,647 --> 00:18:27,690
is the only thing that matters.

236
00:18:44,082 --> 00:18:46,042
What are you waiting for?

237
00:18:49,003 --> 00:18:51,297
Go save the galaxy already.

238
00:18:59,389 --> 00:19:02,433
Whoa. Are those...

239
00:19:02,517 --> 00:19:03,601
Yes.

240
00:19:03,685 --> 00:19:08,273
After Emperor Argall's assassination
and the Purge,

241
00:19:08,356 --> 00:19:11,359
our empire expanded rapidly
as we conquered planets

242
00:19:11,442 --> 00:19:14,279
in memory of the leader we lost.

243
00:19:14,362 --> 00:19:18,825
But it wasn't long
before the scourge virus came

244
00:19:18,908 --> 00:19:20,785
and took almost all of us.

245
00:19:22,704 --> 00:19:25,665
This was the most fitting tomb
we could think of.

246
00:19:26,958 --> 00:19:29,252
Every time we left our home,

247
00:19:29,335 --> 00:19:32,380
we'd be reminded of our weakness

248
00:19:32,463 --> 00:19:34,173
and failure.

249
00:19:34,257 --> 00:19:37,051
They will help
conceal our approach.

250
00:20:00,158 --> 00:20:02,785
Uh... guys?

251
00:20:14,505 --> 00:20:16,758
Well, at least now
we don't need to waste a lot of time

252
00:20:16,841 --> 00:20:18,676
looking for him, right? Heh.

253
00:20:20,428 --> 00:20:22,513
This changes nothing.

254
00:20:31,856 --> 00:20:33,483
They knew we were coming.

255
00:20:34,943 --> 00:20:37,654
It doesn't matter. Kill Thragg!

256
00:20:37,737 --> 00:20:39,656
Yes!

257
00:21:08,017 --> 00:21:08,935
Traitor!

258
00:21:12,397 --> 00:21:14,148
You dare return here--

259
00:21:16,317 --> 00:21:18,444
This bug juice better work!

260
00:21:20,029 --> 00:21:21,197
Huh?

261
00:21:23,783 --> 00:21:25,827
Eat shit!

262
00:21:27,745 --> 00:21:30,748
Okay, it works!
It definitely works!

263
00:21:30,832 --> 00:21:32,834
Great! Shoot someone else!

264
00:21:41,467 --> 00:21:44,345
I should have killed you both
on Thraxa!

265
00:21:49,559 --> 00:21:51,269
The betrayer!

266
00:21:58,151 --> 00:22:00,862
You were always weak, Kregg.

267
00:22:08,119 --> 00:22:09,287
Oliver!

268
00:22:15,668 --> 00:22:17,795
So disappointing.

269
00:22:34,145 --> 00:22:37,065
Your time on Earth has
made you soft.

270
00:22:38,149 --> 00:22:39,233
Don't count on it.

271
00:22:47,283 --> 00:22:48,367
More!

272
00:22:49,494 --> 00:22:50,661
More!

273
00:23:06,552 --> 00:23:09,180
Allen! Get to Thaedus!

274
00:23:11,140 --> 00:23:14,143
What? Oh, shit. On my way!

275
00:23:45,508 --> 00:23:47,969
Kill him before he fires again!

276
00:23:48,052 --> 00:23:51,764
It's not my gun
you should be worried about.

277
00:23:54,225 --> 00:23:55,643
Now!

278
00:24:14,245 --> 00:24:15,246
Allen!

279
00:24:20,626 --> 00:24:21,627
Save the darts!

280
00:24:25,089 --> 00:24:27,758
These things are doing
just fine on their own.

281
00:24:43,524 --> 00:24:44,525
Go!

282
00:25:37,286 --> 00:25:39,789
It's been too long, Nolan.

283
00:25:47,463 --> 00:25:49,006
What do you want, Thragg?

284
00:25:50,091 --> 00:25:52,843
Simply to talk to an old friend.

285
00:25:52,927 --> 00:25:54,679
Since when do we talk?

286
00:25:55,763 --> 00:25:57,348
We've always talked.

287
00:25:58,224 --> 00:26:00,518
Some simply chose not to listen.

288
00:26:01,602 --> 00:26:02,979
Then talk.

289
00:26:06,732 --> 00:26:08,025
Come home, Nolan.

290
00:26:09,277 --> 00:26:11,946
Come home and all will be forgiven.

291
00:26:14,532 --> 00:26:15,783
We have no home.

292
00:26:17,451 --> 00:26:19,370
This place is a tomb.

293
00:26:19,453 --> 00:26:21,747
Viltrum is not a tomb!

294
00:26:23,916 --> 00:26:25,167
Mm.

295
00:26:28,296 --> 00:26:30,464
It is who we are.

296
00:26:32,383 --> 00:26:34,927
We will restore it to what it was,

297
00:26:35,011 --> 00:26:37,805
as we will restore our people
to their rightful place

298
00:26:37,888 --> 00:26:39,807
in the galaxy.

299
00:26:39,890 --> 00:26:42,476
There's barely 40 of us left, Thragg.

300
00:26:44,520 --> 00:26:49,650
Forty Viltrumites who know you
better than you know yourself.

301
00:26:49,734 --> 00:26:51,360
Who have fought beside you.

302
00:26:51,444 --> 00:26:54,405
Who have suffered
exactly the same way you have.

303
00:26:56,324 --> 00:26:58,326
You're not my family anymore.

304
00:26:59,201 --> 00:27:03,581
But the man
who almost caused our extinction is?

305
00:27:03,664 --> 00:27:07,418
I know Thaedus created
the scourge virus.

306
00:27:07,501 --> 00:27:09,503
And yet, you fight beside him.

307
00:27:10,796 --> 00:27:14,175
He committed genocide on his own people.

308
00:27:14,258 --> 00:27:17,595
To stop us from committing it on others.

309
00:27:17,678 --> 00:27:21,599
You know we only ever did
what was necessary to preserve order.

310
00:27:21,682 --> 00:27:23,726
Like coming after my sons?

311
00:27:25,186 --> 00:27:28,230
We tested your sons,
as we have all been tested.

312
00:27:29,398 --> 00:27:33,194
Do you think Thaedus will be
as kind to them if he wins this war?

313
00:27:38,616 --> 00:27:40,117
Ah.

314
00:27:40,201 --> 00:27:43,204
I see you're not as naive as I feared.

315
00:28:06,685 --> 00:28:09,063
Ridiculous creatures.

316
00:28:09,146 --> 00:28:11,482
A distraction at best.

317
00:28:11,565 --> 00:28:15,945
That is what you think
of every species but your own, Lucan.

318
00:28:16,028 --> 00:28:18,531
You'll soon learn better.

319
00:28:57,486 --> 00:28:58,487
Hold on.

320
00:28:58,571 --> 00:29:01,031
Repairing exterior object.

321
00:29:05,703 --> 00:29:07,830
Thank... thank you.

322
00:29:07,913 --> 00:29:10,124
It's all good.
Just keep kicking ass.

323
00:29:17,256 --> 00:29:21,010
This room once echoed
with thousands of voices.

324
00:29:22,470 --> 00:29:27,349
All united with the knowledge
that the universe belonged to Viltrum.

325
00:29:28,350 --> 00:29:30,895
Argall showed us this.

326
00:29:30,978 --> 00:29:33,731
Taught us our true power.

327
00:29:34,899 --> 00:29:36,859
Thaedus...

328
00:29:36,942 --> 00:29:39,403
Thaedus was a coward.

329
00:29:39,487 --> 00:29:41,614
You know that, don't you?

330
00:29:41,697 --> 00:29:43,782
It doesn't change anything.

331
00:29:43,866 --> 00:29:48,120
Fighting for him is
fighting for your own destruction.

332
00:29:48,204 --> 00:29:50,789
Your family's destruction.

333
00:29:50,873 --> 00:29:53,375
I won't let him hurt my family.

334
00:29:54,460 --> 00:29:56,086
You already have.

335
00:29:57,588 --> 00:29:59,632
It's over, Thragg.

336
00:29:59,715 --> 00:30:03,552
The entire galaxy is unified against us.

337
00:30:03,636 --> 00:30:06,138
But it doesn't have to end
with our extinction.

338
00:30:06,222 --> 00:30:09,517
Agree to terms and I will stop this,

339
00:30:09,600 --> 00:30:12,228
no matter what Thaedus wants.

340
00:30:12,311 --> 00:30:15,856
Would our emperor ever agree to terms?

341
00:30:15,940 --> 00:30:18,984
Look around, Thragg.

342
00:30:19,068 --> 00:30:20,986
We lost.

343
00:30:21,070 --> 00:30:23,364
Can't you see why all this fell?

344
00:30:23,447 --> 00:30:26,408
This is our home.

345
00:30:26,492 --> 00:30:28,577
We will rebuild it.

346
00:30:31,121 --> 00:30:32,289
No.

347
00:30:33,374 --> 00:30:35,125
You won't.

348
00:30:38,504 --> 00:30:42,925
The death of any Viltrumite
leaves a void in me.

349
00:30:46,762 --> 00:30:48,597
Uh...

350
00:31:17,501 --> 00:31:19,128
Hey, dickhead!

351
00:31:19,211 --> 00:31:20,546
A black hole called.

352
00:31:22,381 --> 00:31:23,716
It wants its suck back!

353
00:31:26,093 --> 00:31:28,095
You are not one of us.

354
00:31:34,560 --> 00:31:35,477
Oliver!

355
00:31:39,148 --> 00:31:40,524
No!

356
00:31:45,529 --> 00:31:47,489
The child was a failure.

357
00:31:47,573 --> 00:31:49,575
He was no brother to you.

358
00:31:49,658 --> 00:31:51,869
I killed Conquest.

359
00:31:51,952 --> 00:31:53,579
I'll kill you, too.

360
00:31:59,084 --> 00:32:01,003
Show me.

361
00:32:16,226 --> 00:32:18,729
I'm not impressed.

362
00:32:48,384 --> 00:32:49,802
Zoe!

363
00:32:50,719 --> 00:32:51,804
Quick!

364
00:32:55,182 --> 00:32:56,517
Ammunition depleted.

365
00:32:56,600 --> 00:32:58,852
Oh, shit. I'm out.

366
00:33:17,329 --> 00:33:19,248
Kill me if you can,

367
00:33:19,331 --> 00:33:21,834
and die if you cannot,

368
00:33:21,917 --> 00:33:24,253
so I may find a better foe.

369
00:33:24,336 --> 00:33:25,337
Animal.

370
00:33:44,648 --> 00:33:45,691
Finally!

371
00:33:45,774 --> 00:33:47,651
No.

372
00:33:58,704 --> 00:34:01,373
Everyone with me. Now.

373
00:34:20,726 --> 00:34:22,978
Forget him. I need you.

374
00:34:23,061 --> 00:34:25,022
What are we doing?

375
00:34:25,105 --> 00:34:26,857
Space Racer, out front.

376
00:34:36,450 --> 00:34:39,286
No! Stay with me.

377
00:34:44,166 --> 00:34:45,542
No.

378
00:34:46,627 --> 00:34:48,128
No way. We can't.

379
00:34:48,212 --> 00:34:50,380
Mark. Trust me.

380
00:34:51,381 --> 00:34:53,217
Space Racer.

381
00:34:53,300 --> 00:34:54,510
Now!

382
00:34:56,720 --> 00:34:58,096
No.

383
00:34:59,097 --> 00:35:00,265
No!

384
00:35:29,753 --> 00:35:31,171
Keep close.

385
00:35:32,297 --> 00:35:33,757
Hold together!

386
00:36:13,297 --> 00:36:14,631
Whoa.

387
00:40:08,073 --> 00:40:09,157
Zoe!

388
00:40:32,848 --> 00:40:36,810
It was the only way
to show them the truth.

389
00:40:38,687 --> 00:40:40,147
I know.

390
00:40:42,149 --> 00:40:44,151
Oliver. Where's Oliver?

391
00:41:05,547 --> 00:41:07,507
Viltrumites!

392
00:41:07,591 --> 00:41:11,928
Your world is destroyed.

393
00:41:12,012 --> 00:41:16,641
Surrender is your only option.

394
00:41:16,725 --> 00:41:18,685
No!

395
00:41:23,648 --> 00:41:26,902
I choose death!

396
00:41:36,745 --> 00:41:41,958
Emperor Argall, you are avenged.

397
00:41:47,881 --> 00:41:51,301
You are all next.

398
00:41:57,140 --> 00:41:59,768
Thaedus. Oh, God.

399
00:41:59,851 --> 00:42:01,228
Allen.

400
00:42:01,311 --> 00:42:02,729
Find Oliver.

401
00:42:04,064 --> 00:42:05,315
Allen!

402
00:42:05,398 --> 00:42:08,068
Yeah. Yeah, o-okay.

403
00:42:13,657 --> 00:42:16,076
I offered you forgiveness.

404
00:42:16,159 --> 00:42:20,997
I offered you an honorable death.

405
00:42:23,667 --> 00:42:25,293
Instead,

406
00:42:25,377 --> 00:42:28,838
you destroyed everything.

407
00:42:48,858 --> 00:42:51,069
I was too quick with Thaedus.

408
00:42:51,152 --> 00:42:54,406
I won't make the same mistake with you.

409
00:42:58,994 --> 00:43:01,871
Okay. I understand
you are all a little surprised

410
00:43:01,955 --> 00:43:04,457
and upset about what just happened.

411
00:43:06,501 --> 00:43:08,253
Uh, Space Racer?

412
00:43:08,336 --> 00:43:10,171
Space Racer!

413
00:43:51,171 --> 00:43:52,797
Allen!

414
00:43:56,343 --> 00:43:58,178
-  Zoe!
-  It's okay,

415
00:43:58,261 --> 00:43:59,929
I got him.

416
00:44:02,724 --> 00:44:04,351
We have to go.

417
00:44:04,434 --> 00:44:06,686
We can't leave Mark and Nolan.

418
00:44:06,770 --> 00:44:07,937
And where's Oliver?

419
00:44:08,021 --> 00:44:09,481
We can't help them.

420
00:44:47,894 --> 00:44:49,396
You could have been
a Viltrumite...

421
00:44:50,772 --> 00:44:53,400
...but you chose to be noth--

422
00:44:55,527 --> 00:44:58,154
How... how do we beat him?

423
00:44:58,238 --> 00:45:00,615
Mark...

424
00:45:21,636 --> 00:45:23,054
Dad!

425
00:45:26,224 --> 00:45:27,767
What a waste.

426
00:46:18,735 --> 00:46:22,322
Grand Regent, kill him.

427
00:46:22,405 --> 00:46:25,617
They destroyed our home.

428
00:46:25,700 --> 00:46:27,911
Silence.

429
00:46:32,624 --> 00:46:35,919
We are too few already.

430
00:46:45,428 --> 00:46:49,682
What are your orders,
Grand Regent?

431
00:48:17,604 --> 00:48:18,813
Hey.

432
00:48:18,896 --> 00:48:21,149
Hey, buddy. Mark?

433
00:48:21,232 --> 00:48:22,567
You awake?

434
00:48:23,568 --> 00:48:24,819
You are.

435
00:48:24,902 --> 00:48:26,904
Look at that. Welcome back.

436
00:48:29,073 --> 00:48:31,451
Allen. How long...

437
00:48:31,534 --> 00:48:34,996
Couple weeks.
It was touch and go for a while.

438
00:48:35,079 --> 00:48:37,540
Tell you, you guys sure know
how to stress a Unopan out.

439
00:48:42,670 --> 00:48:45,757
Where's Oliver? Where's my dad?

440
00:48:58,227 --> 00:48:59,437
Dad.

441
00:49:06,486 --> 00:49:07,654
You're alive.

442
00:49:07,737 --> 00:49:09,781
Woke up yesterday.

443
00:49:09,864 --> 00:49:11,032
Oliver.

444
00:49:12,116 --> 00:49:14,035
He'll be okay.

445
00:49:14,118 --> 00:49:16,537
He just needs time to heal.

446
00:49:16,621 --> 00:49:18,915
What happened to Thragg and the others?

447
00:49:18,998 --> 00:49:21,668
What's the last thing
you remember?

448
00:49:22,669 --> 00:49:24,379
Thragg had me.

449
00:49:24,462 --> 00:49:26,547
You were... I-I thought you were dead.

450
00:49:27,548 --> 00:49:29,050
Why'd he let us live?

451
00:49:30,051 --> 00:49:32,053
Good question.

452
00:49:32,136 --> 00:49:33,888
But we've got a bigger one.

453
00:49:33,971 --> 00:49:36,891
What? Where are they?

454
00:49:36,974 --> 00:49:39,268
That is the thing.

455
00:49:41,062 --> 00:49:43,106
As all of you know...

456
00:49:45,400 --> 00:49:48,361
Um, as all of you know, Thaedus is dead.

457
00:49:50,321 --> 00:49:53,491
So the council asked someone to lead

458
00:49:53,574 --> 00:49:56,703
until there's time
to appoint his replacement.

459
00:49:56,786 --> 00:50:00,832
And, well, believe it or not,
it's this guy.

460
00:50:00,915 --> 00:50:03,376
They mostly want me to deal
with one small problem.

461
00:50:03,459 --> 00:50:05,336
The remaining Viltrumites.

462
00:50:05,420 --> 00:50:08,047
Yep. General Telia?

463
00:50:08,131 --> 00:50:13,886
We have ships searching sector by sector,
but so far, they've just disappeared.

464
00:50:13,970 --> 00:50:16,597
It's freaking everyone out.

465
00:50:16,681 --> 00:50:19,684
I mean,
the hiding is a good sign, right?

466
00:50:19,767 --> 00:50:23,438
It's not generally
what Viltrumites like to, uh...

467
00:50:23,521 --> 00:50:25,440
Uh, Mark? What's up?

468
00:50:28,443 --> 00:50:30,319
They've gone to Earth.
